{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"content_hash":"fc2810c78118cf7a81c69972befda85ffc081803d5b2650139a66cf27e0a3dfd","digest":{"component_or_area":"reconcile-bridge GitHub Actions signing","key_entities":["REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY","REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY","/rebar/prod/rebar-bot-signing-key","594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","BRIDGE_BOT_EMAIL","reconcile-bridge","rebar verify-identity","gh secret set","ADR-0012"],"problem_keywords":["ci signing","secret provisioning","event signing","identity verification","signed bot events","github actions","ssm secret source"],"propositions":["Set the REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY GitHub secret from the authoritative AWS SSM SecureString source whose public half is registered on identity 594c.","The signing wiring is secret-gated: an empty secret causes unsigned/advisory writes, so correctness is only proven by a run that signs.","Trigger a reconcile-bridge workflow_dispatch run and confirm it advances the tickets branch with bot-authored commits from the bot email.","Verify every non-exempt event the CI run introduced passes rebar verify-identity under enforcement.","This is a provisioning/verification task confirming existing signing wiring, not a workflow-YAML or plumbing change."]},"digest_hash_version":1,"model":"claude-opus-4-8","schema":"ticket_digest_v1"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"TICKET_DIGEST","timestamp":1784242451974110001,"uuid":"9cf67f4d-3915-43ff-b0b0-ac40a4609ed8"}